r||Apps||Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=14|[[Scotland national football team|Scotland]]<ref>{{NFT player|id=12776|name=Brown, Scott|accessdate=11 November 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"eu-football\"/>\n|-\n|2005||1||0\n|-\n|2006||colspan=2|\u2014\n|-\n|2007||7||0\n|-\n|2008||6||0\n|-\n|2009||5||1\n|-\n|2010||3||1\n|-\n|2011||5||0\n|-\n|2012||2||0\n|-\n|2013||7||1\n|-\n|2014||6||1\n|-\n|2015||7||0\n|-\n|2016||2||0\n|-\n|2017||4||0\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\" |Total||55||4\n|}\n\n===International goals===\n:''As of match played 11 November 2016. Scotland score listed first, score column indicates score after each Brown goal.''<ref name=\"eu-football\">{{cite web|url=http://eu-football.info/_player.php?id=26909|title=Scott Brown|publisher=EU-football.info|accessdate=11 November 2016}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ International goals by date, venue, opponent, score, result and competition\n|-\n! Goal || Date || Venue || Opponent || Score || Result || Competition\n|-\n| 1. || 5 September 2009 || [[Hampden Park]], [[Glasgow]] || {{fb|MKD}} || <center> 1\u20130</center> || <center>2\u20130</center> || [[2010 FIFA World Cup qualification \u2013 UEFA Group 9|2010 World Cup qualifier]]\n|-\n| 2. || 3 March 2010 || Hampden Park, Glasgow || {{fb|CZE}} || <center>1\u20130</center> || <center>1\u20130</center> || [[Exhibition game|Friendly]]\n|-\n| 3. || 19 November 2013 || [[Aker Stadion]], [[Molde]] || {{fb|NOR}} || <center>1\u20130</center> || <center>1\u20130</center> || Friendly\n|-\n| 4. || 5 March 2014 || [[National Stadium, Warsaw|National Stadium]], [[Warsaw]] || {{fb|POL}} || <center>1\u20130</center> || <center>1\u20130</center> || Friendly\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n'''Hibernian'''\n*[[Scottish League Cup]]: [[2006\u201307 Scottish League Cup|2006\u201307]]<ref name=\"HibsLC07\" />\n\n'''Celtic'''\n*[[list of Scottish football champions|Scottish Premiership]] (9): [[2007\u201308 Scottish Premier League|2007\u201308]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/scot_prem/7412454.stm|title=Dundee United 0\u20131 Celtic|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|accessdate=5 April 2017}}</ref> [[2011\u201312 Scottish Premier League|2011\u201312]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/17570842|title=Kilmarnock 0\u20136 Celtic|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|accessdate=5 April 2017}}</ref> [[2012\u201313 Scottish Premier League|2012\u201313]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/22409613|title=Celtic 4\u20130 St Johnstone|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|accessdate=5 April 2017}}</ref> [[2013\u201314 Scottish Premiership|2013\u201314]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/26641424|title=Partick Thistle 1\u20135 Celtic|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|accessdate=5 April 2017}}</ref> [[2014\u201315 Scottish Premiership|2014\u201315]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/32664511|title=Celtic 5\u20130 Inverness CT|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|accessdate=5 April 2017}}</ref> [[2015\u201316 Scottish Premier League|2015\u201316]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/36180795|title=Celtic 3\u20132 Aberdeen|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|accessdate=5 April 2017}}</ref> [[2016\u201317 Scottish Premiership|2016\u201317]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/39396454|title=Heart of Midlothian 0\u20135 Celtic|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|accessdate=5 April 2017}}</ref> [[2017\u201318 Scottish Premiership|2017\u201318]]<ref name = \"celtic 50\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/43854076|title=Celtic 5\u20130 Rangers|date=29 April 2018|publisher=BBC|accessdate=29 April 2018|first=Tom|last=English}}</ref> [[2018\u201319 Scottish Premiership|2018\u201319]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/48075065|title=Celtic secured an eighth consecutive title in style with a convincing win away to wasteful Aberdeen.|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|accessdate=4 May 2019}}</ref> \n*[[Scottish Cup]] (5): [[2011 Scottish Cup Final|2010\u201311]],<ref name=\"scup11\" /> [[2013 Scottish Cup Final|2012\u201313]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/22585339|title=Hibernian 0\u20133 Celtic|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|accessdate=5 April 2017}}</ref> [[2016\u201317 Scottish Cup|2016\u201317]],<ref>{{citeweb|url= https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/39984102|title=Celtic 2 Aberdeen 1|date=27 May 2017|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=31 May 2017}}</ref> [[2017\u201318 Scottish Cup|2017\u201318]], [[2018\u201319 Scottish Cup|2018\u201319]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/48318590|title=Heart of Midlothian 1\u20132 Celtic|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|date=25 May 2019 |accessdate=25 May 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Scottish League Cup]] (6): [[2008\u201309 Scottish League Cup|2008\u201309]],<ref name=\"lgcup09\" /> [[2014\u201315 Scottish League Cup|2014\u201315]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/31785677|title=Dundee United 0\u20132 Celtic|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|accessdate=5 April 2017}}</ref> [[2016\u201317 Scottish League Cup|2016\u201317]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/38110297|title=Aberdeen 0\u20133 Celtic|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|accessdate=5 April 2017}}</ref> [[2017\u201318 Scottish League Cup|2017\u201318]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/42056522 |title=Motherwell 0 \u2013 2 Celtic|publisher=BBC Sport |accessdate=26 November 2017 |date=26 November 2017}}</ref> [[2018\u201319 Scottish League Cup|2018\u201319]],<ref name=lc1819/> [[2019\u201320 Scottish League Cup|2019\u201320]]<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/50672183 | title=Rangers 0\u20131 Celtic | publisher=BBC Sport | accessdate=8 December 2019 |date=8 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n'''Individual'''\n*[[PFA Scotland Team of the Year|PFA Scotland Team of the Year (Premiership)]] (6): [[PFA Scotland Team of the Year#Premier League|2006\u201307]],<ref>{{cite web | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/scotland/6584145.stm | title=SPFA's team of the 2006/07 season | publisher=BBC Sport | accessdate=22 May 2017}}</ref> [[PFA Scotland Team of the Year#Premier League 3|2008\u201309]], [[PFA Scotland Team of the Year#Premiership 2|2014\u201315]],<ref>{{cite web | url=http://spfl.co.uk/news/article/pfa-scotland-teams-of-the-year/ | title=PFA Scotland Teams of the Year | publisher=[[SPFL]] | accessdate=22 May 2017 | website= | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150518100706/http://spfl.co.uk/news/article/pfa-scotland-teams-of-the-year | archive-date=18 May 2015 | url-status=dead }}</ref> [[PFA Scotland Team of the Year#Premiership 4|2016\u201317]],<ref>{{cite web | url=http://pfascotland.co.uk/items/PFA-News/pfa-scotland-teams-of-the-year-2017 | title=PFA Scotland teams of the year 2017 | publisher=[[PFA Scotland]] | accessdate=22 May 2017}}</ref> 2017\u201318, [[PFA Scotland Team of the Year#Premiership 6|2018\u201319]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/48171966 |title=James Forrest, Steve Clarke & Ryan Kent win PFA Scotland annual awards |work= |publisher=BBC Sport |date=5 May 2019 |accessdate=5 May 2019}}</ref>\n*[[SFWA Young Player of the Year]]: 2006\u201307\n*[[PFA Scotland Players' Player of the Year]]: 2008\u201309,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/sport/football/scotland/article6217158.ece|title=Celtic's Scott Brown claims player of the year prize |author=Graham Spiers|work=The Times |accessdate=5 May 2009 |date=4 May 2009 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090508021301/http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/sport/football/scotland/article6217158.ece |archivedate=8 May 2009}}</ref> 2017\u201318\n*[[SFWA Footballer of the Year]]: 2017\u201318<ref name = \"sfwa\">[https://www.scottishfwa.com/news/2018/5/11/brown-is-player-of-the-year Brown is Player of the Year], [[Scottish Football Writers' Association]], 11 May 2018</ref>\n*[[Scotland national football team roll of honour]]: 2016<ref name = \"roll\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rsssf.com/tabless/scot-intres2016.html |title=Scotland International Matches 2016 |quote=Scott Brown became the 30th player to reach 50 caps for Scotland. |publisher=Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation |date=1 December 2016 |accessdate=5 April 2017 |first=Gabriele |last=Tossani}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Scott Brown (association football player born June 1985)}}\n* {{SFA profile}}\n* {{CelticFC.net|team/26}}\n* {{NFT player|12776}}\n* {{Soccerway|scott-brown/892}}\n* [http://www.homelessworldcup.com/testimonial/scott-brown/ Homeless World Cup Ambassador Profile]\n\n{{Celtic F.C. squad}}\n{{Navboxes\n| title = Awards\n| bg = gold\n| fg = navy\n| list1 = \n{{2006\u201307 PFA Scotland SPL Team of the Year}}\n{{2008\u201309 PFA Scotland SPL Team of the Year}}\n{{2014\u201315 PFA Scotland Scottish Premiership Team of the Year}}\n{{2016\u201317 PFA Scotland Scottish Premiership Team of the Year}}\n{{2017\u201318 PFA Scotland Scottish Premiership Team of the Year}}\n{{2018\u201319 PFA Scotland Scottish Premiership Team of the Year}}\n{{SPFA Players' Player of the Year}}\n{{SFWA Footballer of the Year}}\n{{SFWA Young Player of the Year}}\n{{Celtic F.C. Player of the Year}}\n}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Brown, Scott (footballer, born 1985 06)}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1985 births]]\n[[Category:People from Hill of Beath]]\n[[Category:People educated at Beath High School]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Fife]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Celtic F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Hibernian F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Scotland B international footballers]]\n[[Category:Scotland international footballers]]\n[[Category:Scotland under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:Scotland youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:Scottish footballers]]\n[[Category:Scottish Premier League players]]\n[[Category:Scottish Professional Football League players]]\n[[Category:Association football players who received a testimonial]]\n", "name_user": "2a00:23c6:ec02:b10