ied in Super Bowl VII, according to the official NFL.com boxscore<ref name=\"Boxscore\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.nfl.com/superbowl/history/boxscore/sbvii |title=Super Bowl VII boxscore |publisher=NFL.com |access-date=November 10, 2016}}</ref> and the ProFootball reference.com game summary.<ref name=\"Stats\" /> Some records have to meet NFL minimum number of attempts to be recognized.<ref name=\"Factbook\">{{cite web | url=http://www.nfl.com/static/content/public/photo/2015/07/21/0ap3000000502939.pdf | title=2016 NFL Factbook | publisher=NFL | accessdate=November 7, 2016}}</ref> The minimums are shown (in parenthesis).\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!colspan=3|Player Records Set in Super Bowl VII <ref name=\"Stats\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.pro-football-reference.com/boxscores/197301140mia.htm |title=Super Bowl VII statistics |publisher=Pro Football reference.com |access-date=November 6, 2016}}</ref>\n|- \n!colspan=3|Rushing Records \n|-  \n|Most yards, career  || 152 yds ||rowspan=3| [[Larry Csonka]] \n|-\n|Longest run from scrimmage || 49 yards   \n|-\n|Highest average gain, career (20 attempts)|| 6.3 yards  (152\u201324)  \n|-\n!colspan=3|Fumbles\n|-\n|Most fumble return yards, game ||rowspan=3 style=\"border-bottom: 2px solid gray\"| 49 yards ||rowspan=4|[[Mike Bass]]{{0}}{{0}}{{0}}<small>(Was)</small>\n|-\n|Longest fumble return  \n|- style=\"border-bottom: 2px solid gray\"\n|Longest fumble return for touchdown   \n|-\n|Most fumble returns for touchdowns, game  || 1  \n|-\n!colspan=3|Defense\n|-\n|Most interception yards gained, game ||rowspan=2| 63 yds||rowspan=2|[[Jake Scott ]]{{0}}{{0}}{{0}}<small>(Mia)</small>\n|-\n|Most interception yards gained, career    \n|-\n!colspan=3|Special Teams \n|- \n|Most kickoff returns, career || 6 ||rowspan=2| [[Mercury Morris]]{{0}}{{0}}{{0}}<small>(Mia)\n|- \n|Most kickoff return yards, career || 123 yds  \n|-\n!colspan=3|Records Tied\n|- style=\"border-bottom: 2px solid gray\"\n|Most interceptions thrown, game || 3 || [[B